avert him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: said [with respect] to him whose aspect, or countenance, thou dislikest. (A, * K.) ―         -b2-  [It is also a proper name for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHad~N","text_ar":"الحَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajaAri","text_ar":"فَجَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfajorapu","text_ar":"الفَجْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfujuwru","text_ar":"الفُجُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in the following hemistich:]"},{"kind":"quote","text":"HadaAdi duwna $ar~ihaA HadaAdi"},{"kind":"text","text":"[May there be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an impediment in the way of her evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief: an impediment"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadaAduka","text_ar":"حَدَادُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n7277","headword_ar":"حُدَادٌ","root":"Hd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiydN","text_ar":"حَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HudaAduka A^ano tafoEala ka*aA","text_ar":"حُدَادُكَ اَنْ تَفْعَلَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) with damm, (TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadaAduka","text_ar":"حَدَادُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in a MS. copy of the K and in the CK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The utmost of thy power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of thine ability,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will be"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy doing such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the end of thy case;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quSaAraAka","text_ar":"قُصَارَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quSaAruka","text_ar":"قُصَارُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munotahaY A^amorika","text_ar":"مُنْتَهَى اَمْرِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n7278","headword_ar":"حِدَادٌ","root":"Hd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black garments of mourning"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worn by a widow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, A, Mgh, L.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n7284","headword_ar":"حَدَّادٌ","root":"Hd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A door-keeper:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, L, Msb, K:) so called because he prevents men from entering. (Mgh, L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A keeper of a prison:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K:) because he prevents persons from going out, or because he works the iron of the shackles. (S. [See what follows.]) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"person who inflicts the punishment termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~N","text_ar":"حَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujorapN AlHad~aAdi EalaY Als~aAriqi","text_ar":"اُجْرَةٌ الحَدَّادِ عَلَى السَّارِقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pay of the inflicter of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hd~","text_ar":"حدّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is to be imposed upon the thief"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; or, as some say, the meaning here is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the keeper of the prison,"},{"kind":"text","text":"because, in general, he has the charge of the amputation; but the former meaning is the more probable, and more obvious. (Mgh.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A seller of wine; a vintner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because he withholds his wine until he obtains for it a price that contents him: so in the following verse of ElAashà:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"faqumonaA walam~aA yaSiHo diykunaA\n                      \n                     \n                        A_ilaY jawonapK Einoda Had~aAdihaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we arose, when our cock had not yet crowed, to a wine-jar smeared with pitch, in the possession of its seller"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, L.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A blacksmith; a worker in iron."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, L, K.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A maker of coats of mail."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","L","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n7285","headword_ar":"حُدَّادٌ","root":"Hd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiydN","text_ar":"حَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}